==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retting
<hw>Ret"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or process of preparing flax for use by soaking, maceration, and kindred
processes; -- also called <altname>rotting</altname>. See
<er>Ret</er>.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where flax is retted; a rettery.</def>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retund</ent>⟦br⟧
